Item.id: RULE://HPMS/1 - Arnold Essential Geometry Checks/Check that Features are Simple

Metadata.Name: Check that Features are Simple
Metadata.Description:
Checks all geometries to determine whether they are simple according to the criteria in "OpenGIS Implementation Specification for Geographic information Simple feature access - Part 1: Common architecture." The criteria applied are: 
-> empty geometries are not OGC simple 
-> a single-Â­part point geometry is OGC simple 
-> a single-part line geometry is OGC simple if it has no self-intersection or self-Â­touch points Exception: an open line with coincident start and end points is OGC simple if it has no other self-intersection or self-Â­touch points 
-> a single-part area geometry is OGC simple if it is OGC valid
-> a multiÂ­-part geometry that contains a mixture of geometry types is not OGC simple 
-> a multi-part point geometry is OGC simple if it contains no coincident single-part point geometries 
-> a multi-part line geometry is OGC simple if none of its components intersect or touch except at open line start/end points. It may not touch other lines 
-> a multiÂ­-part area is OGC simple if it is OGC valid

Item.id: RULE://HPMS/1 - Arnold Essential Geometry Checks/Check that Features are Valid

Metadata.Name: Check that Features are Valid
Metadata.Description:
Checks all geometries to ensure validity according to the OGC definition. The validity criteria are: 
-> empty geometries containing no vertices are invalid 
-> single or multi part point geometries are always valid 
-> single or multi part line geometries are valid if each line consists of at least two non-identical vertices
-> a single-part area geometry is valid if each ring is a valid line with at least three vertices that form a closed shape, the outer ring encloses any inner rings, no ring intersects another ring or itself. A ring may touch another ring at a point, but must not cross it or have any linework in common. A ring must not contain duplicate points
